Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.80,0:00:07.02,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,I hate baths...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:08.16,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.16,0:00:10.42,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wash you if you're \Nmoving around like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.77,0:00:10.42,ngnl-overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.42,0:00:16.43,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,After all that happened today, \Nyou should really take a bath, sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.85,0:00:20.70,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,My hair gets stiff, so I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:23.96,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Then why not use this shampoo?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.49,0:00:27.04,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Where the hell did you come from, Jibril?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:31.04,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Flugel's special \NSpiritwater Blend shampoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:36.51,shampoo2,S,0000,0000,0000,,Spiritwater Blend Shampoo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:36.51,shampoo,S,0000,0000,0000,,Give your hair an elegant finish\Nwith this high-quality shampoo.\NIt maintains luster without\Ndamaging your hair.\N\N{\c&H000000&}Recommended by\NFlugel everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:35.05,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's guaranteed to give your \Nhair a soft, silky-smooth finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.05,0:00:40.97,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,So as your slave, I, Jibril, would be \Nhappy to wash your backs, Masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.50,0:00:44.62,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,The bodies of beings from another world...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:45.01,ngnl-overlap,S,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away from her, Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.64,0:00:46.95,18+,S,0000,0000,0000,,18+
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.01,0:00:46.96,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Her very existence is 18-and-up only!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:49.23,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Jibril, stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.06,0:00:50.92,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.41,0:00:53.76,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,You just sit there and watch, Jibril.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.65,0:00:55.77,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.77,0:00:57.91,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see anything in the steam! No fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.91,0:01:01.53,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,She already has complete \Ncontrol of Jibril as her master.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.97,0:01:00.93,impressed,J,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Your brother\N{\c&H292CCE&}is very\N{\c&H3C6FDE&}impressed!\N{\c&H239CD6&}I wanna be like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.53,0:01:04.12,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Shiro-san. Absolutely awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.12,0:01:07.53,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,I hate the fact that I'm \Nstarting to get used to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.75,0:02:41.74,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.25,0:02:46.57,ngnl-ep-title,T,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1500,420)}Sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.25,0:02:46.74,ngnl-main-top,J,0000,0000,0000,,A kitchen I prepared for my masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.50,0:02:48.64,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Speph-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:49.52,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's Steph!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:50.75,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Stephanie Dola!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.75,0:02:55.28,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in any Imanity \Nother than my masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:56.75,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll call you Dola-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.75,0:02:57.89,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dola?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.89,0:03:00.62,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a message for you from my masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:01.96,ngnl-main-top,J,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Stephanie! I'm Stephanie!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.62,0:03:03.29,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,"There's plenty of sugar and butter here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.29,0:03:05.76,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so make whatever you want," they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.34,0:03:07.95,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.54,0:03:11.50,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,With all this, I could make \Nall kinds of sweets...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:14.76,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that means they're indirectly \Ntelling me to make them something!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.76,0:03:17.28,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're always taking advantage of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:20.20,ngnl-flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for you, we would've lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:21.01,ngnl-flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.17,0:03:23.01,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:27.11,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So this is how the \NImanity experience love.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.11,0:03:28.34,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Love?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.18,0:03:31.74,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.64,0:03:33.75,ngnl-main-top,J,0000,0000,0000,,You were ordered to "fall in love,"\N not "stay in love."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:37.10,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,So why do you still seem to be affected?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.93,0:03:42.13,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,There's no end to the interesting \Nthings going on around my masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.10,0:03:51.57,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, Kurami.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:54.51,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want information? Food?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:57.04,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Or... me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.07,0:04:01.35,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,Clothes first, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.92,0:04:05.32,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,It tastes better than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.67,0:04:08.45,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that things are getting better
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.45,0:04:11.28,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,since the granddaughter \Nof the previous king started
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:14.57,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,putting the new king's policies into effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:15.44,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:17.37,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,Stephanie Dola did that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.43,0:04:20.09,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,A puppet of a puppet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.09,0:04:22.51,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,She's as shameless as her \Ngrandfather was foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:25.53,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,The way you're upset about \Nhow you were mean to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.53,0:04:30.84,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,and secretly practicing how you'd \Napologize to her, is really cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.84,0:04:32.14,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.14,0:04:35.19,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,I mean... More importantly, \Ndon't you have any information?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:37.13,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.13,0:04:40.86,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,The only other things are that \Nthe new king's got a Flugel now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:45.00,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,and that he's interested \Nin the Eastern Federation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.37,0:04:46.66,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:51.40,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,I got a little too into it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.86,0:04:54.35,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,B-But this will benefit \NImanity in the long term.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.35,0:04:57.04,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely not love or anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.83,0:04:59.66,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Jibril-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.66,0:05:02.70,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me everything you know \Nabout the Eastern Federation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:05.05,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,this animal girl paradise I'm about to conquer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.05,0:05:07.42,ngnl-internal,T,0000,0000,0000,,This country is doomed already, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.86,0:05:09.39,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.10,0:05:14.80,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,The various clans of Warbeasts \Nwere in a state of civil war
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:17.89,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,for many years, due to \Ntheir physical differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.89,0:05:20.67,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,An individual known as the \NShrine Priestess ended the war
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:22.30,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,in under half a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:23.85,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,uniting the many clans
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.85,0:05:26.37,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,into a massive naval empire and the \Nthird biggest country in the world:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:27.90,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the Eastern Federation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.90,0:05:30.67,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, it's a country of \Ngirls with cat ears, dog ears,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.67,0:05:35.71,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,fox ears, rabbit ears, and all other kinds \Nof ears, and they're all going to be mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.71,0:05:37.79,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll attack and \Noverthrow them immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:43.18,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,To do that, we need the knowledge \Nthat you've spent millennia building!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.13,0:05:46.99,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:52.19,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid that even you may not be \Nable to defeat the Eastern Federation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.07,0:05:54.63,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Jibril, are you saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.32,0:05:56.90,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,...that "Blank" will lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.25,0:06:02.20,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm saying I won't be able to help you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:05.61,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,because I once challenged \Nthe Eastern Federation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.08,0:06:07.15,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.79,0:06:09.89,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,That settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.49,0:06:15.09,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,The Eastern Federation, and the \NWarbeasts, are backing Elkia now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.09,0:06:17.42,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:19.16,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, don't you, Fi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:24.14,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,Elven Garde challenged the \NEastern Federation four times,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:26.13,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and lost each time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.64,0:06:31.04,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was those senile \Nelders that lost, but yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.59,0:06:34.49,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,It explains how those two beat a Flugel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:38.94,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and how they beat me when \NI had an elf's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.41,0:06:42.38,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,If the Warbeasts are behind them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:45.52,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,they could easily be using some trick \Nthat even an elf can't see through.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.04,0:06:48.19,ngnl-main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Kurami...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.19,0:06:50.12,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.12,0:06:53.32,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Imanity could never beat a higher race alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:57.48,ngnl-flashbackinternal,S,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.12,0:07:01.40,ngnl-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,He mocked me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.38,0:07:06.33,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,So an elf can't even beat them, \Nlet alone a Flugel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.33,0:07:08.68,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of game did you play?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.03,0:07:11.63,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Their bet is that the loser
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.63,0:07:14.65,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,will have their memories of the game wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.65,0:07:16.05,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Now do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.77,0:07:18.99,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I see. No way to beat that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.99,0:07:20.65,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:36.39,pity,T,0000,0000,0000,,Eyes filled with pity
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:36.39,games,T,0000,0000,0000,,Game: Rock-Paper-Scissors
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.10,0:07:22.74,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,If your memories are wiped out,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.74,0:07:24.17,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,no records of what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.64,0:07:25.14,mem,T,0000,0000,0000,,Memories
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.17,0:07:26.13,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,during the game would remain, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.13,0:07:28.06,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,You can't make a plan to beat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.06,0:07:30.97,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, they can supposedly read minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.97,0:07:32.36,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you beat that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.35,0:07:36.39,info,T,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)}Information
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.36,0:07:35.07,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,We just told you that information is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.07,0:07:36.40,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you really are a Steph.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.84,0:07:39.09,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.09,0:07:40.41,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.41,0:07:41.04,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,What doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:44.38,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,If no one ever came close to beating them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:46.68,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,then people would stop challenging them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:49.70,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be easier not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.70,0:07:52.55,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Little sister, that's why you \Nlose at strategy games,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.55,0:07:54.10,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,even though you're smarter than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.10,0:07:54.69,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Grr.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.18,0:07:59.05,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,They've got something that lets \Nthem beat the elves and the Flugel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.05,0:08:01.43,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,They could do better if they \Nshowed a little vulnerability,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.43,0:08:04.82,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,lured the enemy into attacking, \Nand then took their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.82,0:08:05.43,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.43,0:08:08.04,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Your play style is obnoxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.04,0:08:08.93,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Brother shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.64,0:08:11.76,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,But you're right, it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:15.23,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way they could expand their \Ncountry this much in a half century.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.23,0:08:15.98,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.98,0:08:17.04,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.25,0:08:20.78,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I think I can explain that, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.28,0:08:22.56,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.56,0:08:23.59,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:26.47,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,It was in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.47,0:08:31.46,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,In the past ten years, only one country \Nchallenged the Eastern Federation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.46,0:08:33.99,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,What idiotic country did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:36.59,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,It would be faster to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.59,0:08:38.60,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Dola-chan will come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.00,0:08:42.60,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Come, grab on to me, Masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:45.60,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Now, please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.27,0:09:01.75,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.75,0:09:04.14,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice and clear today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:05.17,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.17,0:09:06.73,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:08.46,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I teleported us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:09.73,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.73,0:09:12.43,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's right... We're in a \Nreal fantasy world, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:14.60,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,How far can you go with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.98,0:09:17.04,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I can go anywhere in my field of vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.04,0:09:19.09,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,or anywhere I've been once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.09,0:09:20.44,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's a "zoom" spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.84,0:09:25.83,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,How did the Imanity survive the \Nancient war against these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.83,0:09:28.81,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's considered the greatest \Nmystery in human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.81,0:09:31.95,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember the ancient war!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:36.52,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,The Dragonia, Gigant, and Old Deus \Nstorming around the battlefield,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.52,0:09:39.58,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,fifty Flugel banding together and barely \Nmanaging to kill a single dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.58,0:09:42.64,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,or 200 of us taking on a god and losing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:45.92,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,What wonderful memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.82,0:09:49.50,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,But forget that. Look over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:51.89,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.89,0:09:55.40,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,What's that skyscraper doing \Nmessing up the Elkian landscape?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:56.29,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.29,0:09:59.04,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Eastern Federation's Elkian Embassy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:02.19,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a building.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:07.05,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,It was actually the former palace, \Nand the Eastern Federation rebuilt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.05,0:10:08.32,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.66,0:10:11.47,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you just said "former" palace, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.47,0:10:12.63,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.63,0:10:14.90,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:18.50,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,The only country to challenge the Eastern \NFederation over the past ten years...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:21.22,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're not telling me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.22,0:10:24.26,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it was Elkia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.86,0:10:28.53,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.53,0:10:29.97,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Sorry, Shiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.97,0:10:32.61,zetsubou,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Despair
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.28,0:10:32.06,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just in despair, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.61,0:10:38.11,map,S,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Federation      Modern Elkia      Old Territory
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.04,0:10:35.58,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,The elves challenged these \Nguys and lost four times,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.58,0:10:38.83,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,and Elkia challenged them eight \Ntimes and lost half their territory?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.83,0:10:41.59,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the old king really was an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.59,0:10:42.66,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:46.12,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,You said before that he was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:49.62,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He threw away half the country's \Nterritory for no reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:50.99,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to defend that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.68,0:10:54.40,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea how much \Nagriculture and industry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:10:57.04,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,we could build if we had that territory?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:10:58.98,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He really is your grandpa, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.64,0:11:01.42,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Did he believe in luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.98,0:11:01.15,bet,S,0000,0000,0000,,What She Bet
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.42,0:11:04.16,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and figure that, if he just kept \Ntrying, he'd win eventually?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.54,0:11:08.93,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,He may not have been good at games,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:12.97,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,but he wasn't crazy enough \Nto gamble with the lives of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.97,0:11:14.80,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,three million Imanity for no reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.68,0:11:18.67,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,He was a good, sane man, unlike you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.10,0:11:21.42,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,A good, sane man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.31,0:11:25.73,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,If losing half your territory \Nfor no reason makes you "sane,"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.73,0:11:27.45,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stay nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.31,0:11:32.26,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he may be a good \Nking for a people that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.26,0:11:36.06,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,does nothing but complain when \Nit's their own lives on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.04,0:11:41.32,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity's past saving, seriously. \NEvery last one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:48.41,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if you insult me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.03,0:11:53.10,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,but don't insult my grandfather \Nor the things he believed in!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.10,0:11:56.71,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.26,0:11:58.34,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Steph!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.92,0:12:00.95,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, that was going too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.60,0:12:06.35,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,After the unbelievable reality she just \Nshowed me, what was I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.18,0:12:13.98,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:21.13,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.92,0:12:24.00,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,It really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:35.51,ngnl-flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather, what is this key for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.04,0:12:40.26,ngnl-flashback,King,0000,0000,0000,,It's the key to where I keep \Nsomething very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.26,0:12:41.90,ngnl-flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,I know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:44.62,ngnl-flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard men collect books they \Ncan't show to other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.62,0:12:46.74,ngnl-flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's another key...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.74,0:12:48.17,ngnl-flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.17,0:12:51.04,ngnl-flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,This is a key of hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:52.20,ngnl-flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:54.99,ngnl-flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, I'll give this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.99,0:12:56.64,ngnl-flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.20,0:12:58.34,ngnl-flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.73,0:13:01.03,ngnl-flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, when you meet someone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:06.47,ngnl-flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,you can truly entrust with \NElkia's fate, give it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.59,0:13:12.88,ngnl-internal,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not giving it to that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:15.10,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,May I have a word?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.13,0:13:18.67,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.22,0:13:22.97,ngnl-main-top,J,0000,0000,0000,,I would recommend you return \Nto the library immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.67,0:13:20.21,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's trespassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:23.93,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.93,0:13:27.42,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I've determined that this would be best \Nfor my master, and acted on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.42,0:13:29.66,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,You may do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:30.26,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.86,0:13:34.70,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:36.16,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.00,0:13:45.01,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, for crying out loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.05,0:13:58.46,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Master, no matter how hard you look,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.46,0:14:01.45,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you'll find anything \Nto justify the former king's actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.45,0:14:03.58,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.58,0:14:05.16,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I just realized something felt off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:08.73,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you were thinking \Nabout it for Dola-chan's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.73,0:14:11.34,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I was just going back over it so
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.34,0:14:14.44,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what not to do when \NI challenge the animal girl kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.44,0:14:18.68,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd he challenge them eight times, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.93,0:14:21.63,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,A sane man in charge of the lives \Nof three million people wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:23.95,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,just rush into defeat that many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:27.88,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place the previous \Nking bet the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:29.69,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,An Armatite mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.93,0:14:31.66,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's a valuable metal,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.66,0:14:35.80,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,but with Imanity's current technology, \Nwe can't even use it, so it's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.80,0:14:37.25,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then the second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.25,0:14:38.51,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,the third time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.51,0:14:39.77,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,the fourth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.77,0:14:42.19,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,And the eighth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.51,0:14:44.95,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Until the last time, when he bet the castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.95,0:14:47.34,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the king didn't bet a single thing of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:50.33,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.82,0:14:51.74,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:55.30,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why does the Eastern Federation wipe players' \Nmemories when that only hurts them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:57.48,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why did Elven Garde \Nchallenge them four times?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:14:59.40,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the previous king...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:01.29,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.29,0:15:03.00,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Did he stop after eight times
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:06.59,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,because he'd achieved his goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:12.52,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any proof, but what \Nif he didn't lose his memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:13.16,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:16.33,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:21.27,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,but not all the Imanity act with the \Nsame level of thought that you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.64,0:15:23.84,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,But some of them do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.84,0:15:26.93,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,And most of the time, they're misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.93,0:15:30.02,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's my duty to try and understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.90,0:15:32.18,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,You can say what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.59,0:15:36.63,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,How can you believe in a lesser \Nlife form like humanity?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.63,0:15:38.31,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,No, I wasn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.31,0:15:39.61,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:43.39,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe in humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.17,0:15:49.86,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are lowly, stupid creatures. \NEvery single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.66,0:15:51.76,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.89,0:15:54.88,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're all crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.88,0:15:58.27,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Between this world and the old one, \Nthat hasn't changed a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.48,0:16:05.52,ngnl-internal,T,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. I can't let that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.02,0:16:09.23,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe in the potential of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.46,0:16:09.23,shirt,T,0000,0000,0000,,I {\c&H4F4FE1&}♥ {\c&H484E87&}Humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.53,0:16:13.94,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,She's my proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:16.71,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them are the real thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.15,0:16:20.72,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,People with the potential, \Nthe hope, the fantasies
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.72,0:16:24.44,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,that can reach the gods themselves, \Nall inside one tiny little body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.11,0:16:28.83,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,The first day I met Shiro... \NIt was eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.79,0:16:31.83,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,She was just three years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:35.70,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,When she heard my name, what \Ndo you think her first response was?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.38,0:16:39.35,ngnl-flashback,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,You really are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.06,0:16:44.68,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,She put together my name, \NSora, meaning "sky,"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.68,0:16:48.21,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and the fact that I was only \Nsmiling because everybody else was,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.21,0:16:50.43,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,and insulted me with that double meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.43,0:16:51.32,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Funny, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.02,0:16:54.30,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,It made my heart pound. I was so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:56.80,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,The real thing actually existed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.44,0:16:58.33,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:02.47,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,even though I knew it was impossible, \NI wanted to be like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.72,0:17:07.37,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,In our old world, humans \Ncould fly through the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.37,0:17:08.99,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and travel among the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.99,0:17:11.33,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.33,0:17:14.42,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, even humanity \Nthemselves, thought that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.77,0:17:16.21,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,But somebody did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.21,0:17:18.97,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody, the real thing, made it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.20,0:17:24.80,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's our job as normal people \Nto ensure that the potential of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.80,0:17:26.49,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,those misunderstood ones is realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.17,0:17:32.23,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why I need to start by \Nbelieving in the old king, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.60,0:17:45.34,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sora...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.03,0:17:58.54,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,I want to give you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.97,0:18:01.32,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.13,0:18:03.01,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's his porn stash!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.01,0:18:06.01,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. My life was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.08,0:18:07.97,ngnl-overlap,J,0000,0000,0000,,But where's the door it goes to, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.97,0:18:10.16,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,You hide your porn in your own room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.50,0:18:12.05,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,That would be this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:14.40,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we found it a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.03,0:18:15.21,ngnl-overlap,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,V.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.89,0:18:18.85,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Remember when I said this bed \Nwas tilted and hard to sleep on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.47,0:18:21.77,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That was the start of the puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.77,0:18:23.79,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then you just fiddle with some things...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:30.16,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,and there's your secret room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:34.22,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a failure on so many levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.38,0:19:09.01,ngnl-internal,K,0000,0000,0000,,I leave this in hopes that you will not \Nbe Imanity's last king, but the one
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.01,0:19:10.43,ngnl-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,that will restore them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:13.68,ngnl-internal,K,0000,0000,0000,,I am not a wise king.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:18.34,ngnl-internal,K,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I expect that I will be \Nremembered as one of the most foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.09,0:19:25.51,ngnl-internal,K,0000,0000,0000,,But I take up my pen for the \Nking who will restore our glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.33,0:19:35.29,ngnl-internal,K,0000,0000,0000,,I trust and hope that my pathetic, \Nhopeless struggles will aid you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:38.45,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:41.76,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,The old king didn't lose his memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.46,0:19:46.09,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the elves, lower life \Nforms like the Imanity were
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.09,0:19:48.31,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,nothing but easy prey to the Warbeasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.73,0:19:52.10,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't erase his memories because \Nthey wanted him to keep trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.91,0:19:54.92,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,They wanted to lure him in and beat him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:19:56.70,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,They deliberately went easy on him
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.70,0:19:59.35,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to make him believe he \Ncould beat them next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:03.90,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,But the previous king knew that \Nand challenged them anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.90,0:20:05.96,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,hoping to find out how their game worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.66,0:20:08.74,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He deliberately gave them \Nuseless land in order
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.74,0:20:10.27,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to eventually take it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.92,0:20:15.97,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Then why didn't he tell the \Nsecret of the game to anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.97,0:20:18.32,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably forced to pledge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:21.45,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,that he'd never tell anyone \Nas long as he lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.30,0:20:23.80,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,But then what was the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:24.36,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.75,0:20:28.05,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,that doesn't apply after he's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.52,0:20:33.09,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He bet eight times and found \Na loophole in the pledges,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.09,0:20:35.70,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,and entrusted it to a king that \Nwould restore humanity...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.21,0:20:39.55,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,To humanity's greatest gambler.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:45.15,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,That was why he held a gambling \Ntournament to determine the next king?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.44,0:20:47.65,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He made a bet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.83,0:20:51.24,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,that a human, the lowest-ranked race,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:54.09,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,would appear who could defeat the other races.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:20:58.14,ngnl-flashbackinternal,K,0000,0000,0000,,The possibility is so ever close to zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.14,0:21:01.90,ngnl-flashbackinternal,,0000,0000,0000,,but it isn't zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.14,0:21:05.03,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Steph.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.25,0:21:09.31,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather was a great man \Nwho pretended to be a fool,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.31,0:21:10.59,ngnl-main,,0000,0000,0000,,challenged and lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.59,0:21:14.80,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,and devoted himself to finding \Nhis opponent's secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.20,0:21:20.21,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is his trust in humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.97,0:21:26.19,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather, no, the previous king...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.18,0:21:31.19,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,He really was your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.54,0:21:34.75,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.30,0:21:36.89,ngnl-main,T,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.57,0:21:43.43,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's a heavy thing he's given us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.25,0:21:45.40,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.90,0:21:47.47,ngnl-main,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,You and I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.71,0:21:50.04,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,See, Jibril?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.75,0:21:52.82,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are humans like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.81,0:21:56.82,shirt2,S,0000,0000,0000,,I {\c&H4F4FE1&}♥ \N{\c&H484E87&}Humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.13,0:21:56.82,ngnl-main,S,0000,0000,0000,,Crazy, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.58,0:22:04.39,ngnl-main,J,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.95,0:23:45.96,ngnl-next-ep-title,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Fake End
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.76,0:23:45.96,ngnl-main-top,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Federation, your head would \Nlook good on the end of a pole!
